<section xml:id="section-add-and-subtract-polynomials">

    <title>Add/Subtract Polynomials</title>

    <introduction>
    	<p>Let's start by looking at some applications of polynomials:<ul>
    		<li><p>A company's sales can be modeled by the equation <m>s=2.2t+5.8</m>, where <m>t</m> stands for the number of years since <m>2010</m>, and <m>y</m> stands for dollars in millions.</p></li>
    		<li><p>The height of an object launched upward on top of a building can be modeled by the equation <m>h=-16t^2+16t+300</m>, where <m>t</m> stands for the time in seconds since the launch, and <m>h</m> stands for the object's height.</p></li>
    		<li><p>The volume of a container can be calculated by <m>v=\frac{4}{3}\pi r^3+10r^2</m>, where <m>r</m> stands for the radius of a sphere part in feet, and <m>v</m> stands for its volume in cubic feet.</p></li>
    	</ul></p>

    	<p>All those equations are in the form of <term>polynomials</term>. In this section, we will learn some basic terms of polynomials, and then learn how to add/subtract them.</p>

